INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (486051, 'As a society we''re always so quick and able to spend money on lawyers for someone for incarceration, but we don''t make the corresponding commitment to the preventative components of it.', 75477, 0), (486052, 'We are now after 7 months operation making money here.', 75478, 0), (486053, 'Now Congress learns that the Veterans Administration failed to provide complete, accurate information on the money it needs for both this year and next year.', 68655, 0), (486054, 'San Francisco is an interesting place. It''s always been such a nice culturally diverse environment, which it still is, but there''s a lot of money there now and a lot of dot com''s so it''s a little different than it used to be.', 60044, 0), (486055, 'Money can add very much to one''s ability to lead a constructive life, not only pleasant for oneself, but, hopefully, beneficial to others.', 73000, 0), (486056, 'When I was younger I was completely without money - when I was studying in Budapest, when I was a refugee.', 20227, 0), (486057, 'I really wish there was some big brother conspiracy theory. I just think it''s the ignorance of trying to make a dollar. That''s what the networks have done and will continue to do. If anyone doesn''t think that this is about making money, then they''re crazy.', 72059, 0), (486058, 'American men, as a group, seem to be interested in only two things, money and breasts. It seems a very narrow outlook.', 12987, 0), (486059, 'The black groups that boycott certain films would do better to get the money together to make the films they want to see, or stay in church and leave us to our work.', 2259, 0), (486060, 'And, we have no such thing as a budget anymore. Our manager freaks when we show him the bill. We''re lavish to the bone, but all our money goes back into the product.', 7810, 0), (486061, 'Law students have taken over Hollywood. To them it''s all about making money. They know people want to see what they''ve seen before. Also, remakes are places to showcase the new stars of tomorrow.', 41177, 0), (486062, 'Fame was thrilling only until it became grueling. Money was fun only until you ran out of things to buy.', 49634, 0), (486063, 'We are the nation the most powerful, the most armed and we are supplying arms and money to the rest of the world where we are not ourselves fighting. We are eating while there is famine in the world.', 848, 0), (486064, 'Money is the great tool through whose means labor and skill become universally co-operative.', 66810, 0), (486065, 'We got more provisions for our whiskey than the same money, which we paid for the liquor, would have bought; so after all it proved a very profitable investment.', 69032, 0), (486066, 'I had a great time on News Radio, I got to make tons of money in relative obscurity and learn a lot about the TV biz and work on my standup act constantly. It was a dream gig.', 43216, 0), (486067, 'The way I grew up, I was always taught that it''s uncouth to talk about money, and that''s not what should inspire you.', 58477, 0), (486068, 'No matter how much money you have or what kind of cocoon you live in, the reality is that you have lost a game of football and let England''s fans down. We are bothered.', 75479, 0), (486069, 'A little wanton money, which burned out the bottom of his purse.', 2628, 0), (486070, 'We talk about a free press. These people hide, they make a lot of money off the media. They hide behind the slogans of free press, and then they can come out with crap like that. It''s just garbage. It''s insulting to the readers.', 75480, 0), (486071, 'I have heartaches, I have blues. No matter what you got, the blues is there. ''Cause that''s all I know - the blues. And I can sing the blues so deep until you can have this room full of money and I can give you the blues.', 10307, 0), (486072, 'Happy is harder than money. Anybody who thinks money will make you happy hasn''t got money.', 66831, 0), (486073, 'Because parents have power over children. They feel they have to do what their parents say. But the love of money is the root of all evil. And this is a sweet child. And to see him turn like this, this isn''t him. This is not him.', 646, 0), (486074, 'And my father didn''t have money for me to go to college. And at that particular time they didn''t have black quarterbacks, and I don''t think I could have made it in basketball, because I was only 5'' 11". So I just picked baseball.', 64941, 0), (486075, 'I like to sing ballads the way Eddie Fisher does and the way Perry Como does. But the way I''m singing now is what makes the money.', 1120, 0), (486076, 'The rich man who gives, steals twice over. First he steals the money and then the hearts of men.', 7791, 0), (486077, 'Money may kindle, but it cannot by itself, and for very long, burn.', 16868, 0), (486078, 'I make a lot of money and I''m worth every cent.', 27363, 0), (486079, 'I like my money right where I can see it... hanging in my closet.', 4816, 0), (486080, 'There''s so little money in my bank account, my scenic checks show a ghetto.', 2181, 0), (486081, 'Always remember, money isn''t everything - but also remember to make a lot of it before talking such fool nonsense.', 25666, 0), (486082, 'But if inventions have increased man''s power over nature very much, then the real value of money is better measured for some purposes in labour than in commodities.', 52683, 0), (486083, 'Having money is rather like being a blond. It is more fun but not vital.', 57412, 0), (486084, 'A fool and his money are lucky enough to get together in the first place.', 75481, 0), (486085, 'Because people have no thoughts to deal in, they deal cards, and try and win one another''s money. Idiots!', 1304, 0), (486086, 'When you''re on a series, it''s tough to go on and do something else afterward. If you''re smart, save your money and you can wait out the bad times, until something else comes along.', 75482, 0), (486087, 'It is time for u