blic education is our greatest pathway to opportunity in America. So we need to invest in and strengthen our public universities today, and for generations to come.', 1997, 0), (486316, 'You may be a redneck if... you have spent more on your pickup truck than on your education.', 1491, 0), (486317, 'A system of education is not one thing, nor does it have a single definite object, nor is it a mere matter of schools. Education is that whole system of human training within and without the school house walls, which molds and develops men.', 3227, 0), (486318, 'That''s the value of a college education... I don''t know anywhere in the world where you can make an investment and make that kind of return.', 67396, 0), (486319, 'Learn to think continentally.', 16733, 0), (486320, 'I believe that education is all about being excited about something. Seeing passion and enthusiasm helps push an educational message.', 15778, 0), (486321, 'To defend a country you need an army, but to defend a civilization you need education.', 4059, 0), (486322, 'Education''s purpose is to replace an empty mind with an open one.', 5930, 0), (486323, 'All I want is an education, and I am afraid of no one.', 1851, 0), (486324, 'To accuse others for one''s own misfortunes is a sign of want of education. To accuse oneself shows that one''s education has begun. To accuse neither oneself nor others shows that one''s education is complete.', 1328, 0), (486325, 'The idea of education has been so tied to schools, universities, and professors that many assume there is no other way, but education is available to anyone within reach of a library, a post office, or even a newsstand.', 1682, 0), (486326, 'Education is our only political safety. Outside of this ark all is deluge.', 2053, 0), (486327, 'The education of a man is never completed until he dies.', 1924, 0), (486328, 'I need to complete my homework on time.', 1851, 0), (486329, 'Reformation, like education, is a journey, not a destination.', 1505, 0)