orrow''s workforce by guaranteeing every child access to a world-class education.', 1693, 0), (486376, 'If you want to be an anthropologist, you need to study physical anthropology specialized in bones. If you want to be a forensic chemist, get a degree in chemistry. Do you want to do DNA work? Get a degree in microbiology. And do well. Study hard and go to graduate school.', 2294, 0), (486377, 'Prejudices, it is well known, are most difficult to eradicate from the heart whose soil has never been loosened or fertilized by education; they grow firm there, firm as weeds among stones.', 42, 0), (486378, 'The highest education is that which does not merely give us information but makes our life in harmony with all existence.', 430, 0), (486379, 'The most valuable of all education is the ability to make yourself do the thing you have to do, when it has to be done, whether you like it or not.', 1032, 0), (486380, 'It is only as we develop others that we permanently succeed.', 19497, 0), (486381, 'Economists report that a college education adds many thousands of dollars to a man''s lifetime income - which he then spends sending his son to college.', 5968, 0), (486382, 'You can''t continue to have higher education tuition grow at a multiple of the rate of inflation.', 52321, 0), (486383, 'Education, housing and hospitals are the most important things for society.', 68727, 0), (486384, 'Cutting the deficit by gutting our investments in innovation and education is like lightening an overloaded airplane by removing its engine. It may make you feel like you''re flying high at first, but it won''t take long before you feel the impact.', 1693, 0), (486385, 'Education and work are the levers to uplift a people.', 3227, 0), (486386, 'So if a college education is indispensable, the challenge as I see it is how to make it more accessible.', 68475, 0), (486387, 'The things I want to know are in books my best friend is the man who''ll get me a book I ain''t read. ', 1012, 0), (486388, 