e US economy without a great education system. Teach students to do the job right. You don''t have an innovative economy unless you have a great education.', 1992, 0), (486626, 'One of the greatest obstacles to escaping poverty is the staggering cost of higher education.', 74017, 0), (486627, 'I think more of the little kids from a school in a little village in Niger who get teaching two hours a day, sharing one chair for three of them, and who are very keen to get an education. I have them in my mind all the time. Because I think they need even more help than the people in Athens.', 66813, 0), (486628, 'Our solution on ''The Simpsons'' is to do jokes that people who have an education, or some frame of reference, can get. And for the ones who don''t, it doesn''t matter, because we have Homer banging his head and saying, ''D''oh!''', 538, 0), (486629, 'I really don''t want you to think of Qatar as a hydrocarbon country alone. We know that hydrocarbons will come and go. But education will stay. It is the most important thing for us.', 75110, 0), (486630, 'Education is key. I graduated from high school everyone needs to. ', 75521, 0), (486631, 'When you have a father and a mother who work all their lives so you can have an education and build your body - it''s a blessing.', 69220, 0), (486632, 'It is possible to get an education at a university. It has been done not often. ', 27571, 0), (486633, 'The American dream always meant that anybody willing to put in a hard day''s work could make a decent living. That''s just not true anymore for people without at least some post-high school education.', 69148, 0), (486634, 'Education is when you read the fine print. Experience is what you get if you don''t.', 22827, 0), (486635, 'Good education, housing and jobs are imperatives for the Negroes, and I shall support them in their fight to win these objectives, but I shall tell the Negroes that while these are necessary, they cannot solve the main Negro problem.', 1730, 0), (486636, 'Instead of saving for someone else''s college education, I''m currently saving for a luxury retirement community replete with golf carts and handsome young male nurses who love butterscotch.', 49833, 0), (486637, 'In school, many of us procrastinate and then successfully cram for tests. We get the grades and degrees we need to get the jobs we want, even if we fail to get a good general education.', 10390, 0), (486638, 'In order to invest in our future, we must ensure that we appropriately protect programs that provide skills, services, and education for middle-class Americans rather than providing tax breaks for large corporations.', 75522, 0), (486639, 'My father superintended the English part of my education, and to his care I am indebted for anything valuable which I may have acquired in my youth. He was my only intelligent companion, and was both a watchful parent and an affectionate friend.', 16764, 0), (486640, 'A big part of my life is music education because it changed my life - but arts, academics and athletics should all be equally treated in the school.', 71038, 0), (486641, 'The Nazi period could have happened only in Germany because the German education of obedience to any law and order was the main problem.', 10560, 0), (486642, 'From China and India to Turkey and Brazil, when women have gotten access to education, to family planning and to a vital place in the economy, greater prosperity has followed. And when women are free to speak and learn, they temper the extremes of ideology and fanaticism and raise sons who are less likely to become human bombs.', 67465, 0), (486643, 'I''m a gypsy: no education, no schooling, nothing. I don''t care what people think of me. I don''t care about being a hero, a role model, a champion.', 67829, 0), (486644, 'Everything that makes man''s life worthwhile - family, work, education, a place to rear one''s children and a place to rest one''s head - all this depends on the decisions of government; all can be swept away by a government which does not heed the demands of its people, and I mean all of its people.', 60667, 0), (486645, 'Education is our greatest opportunity to give an irrevocable gift to the next generation.', 75523, 0), (486646, 'Through first-class education, a generation marches down the long uncertain road of the future with confidence.', 22730, 0), (486647, 'The primary purpose of a liberal education is to make one''s mind a pleasant place in which to spend one''s leisure.', 4317, 0), (486648, 'We look for people who demonstrate perseverance in the face of challenges, the ability to influence and motivate others - people who want to work relentlessly to ensure that kids who are facing the challenges of poverty have an excellent education.', 67447, 0), (486649, 'The work of popular education, the temperance movement, the peace movement, are to a great extent carried on by the young. Their meetings show that the young understand one of their tasks: that of bringing together the different classes through social intercourse.', 62381, 0), (486650, 'We talk about what''s important to Hispanics: education, family, creating an environment in which you can achieve what you want to achieve because there aren''t going to be obstacles in your way.', 68223, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (486651, 'What sculpture is to a block of marble, education is to the soul.', 2868, 0), (486652, 'It is well to read everything of something, and something of everything.', 1254, 0), (486653, 'Books are the blessed chloroform of the mind.', 1903, 0), (486654, 'The object of education is to prepare the young to educate themselves throughout their lives.', 64234, 0), (486655, 'You can educate yourself right out of a relationship with God.', 72029, 0), (486656, 'To the extent that we are all educated and informed, we will be more equipped to deal with the gut issues that tend to divide us.', 10105, 0), (486657, 'The mere imparting of information is not education.', 3302, 0), (486658, 'Before the child ever gets to school it will have received crucial, almost irrevocable sex education and this will have been taught by the parents, who are not aware of what they are doing.', 75524, 0), (486659, 'In these days, it is doubtful that any child may reasonably be expected to succeed in life if he is denied the opportunity of an education.', 17567, 0), (486660, 'Any education that matters is liberal. All the saving truths, all the healing graces that distinguish a good education from a bad one or a full education from a half empty one are contained in that word.', 75525, 0), (486661, 'His lack of education is more than compensated for by his keenly developed moral bankruptcy.', 281, 0), (486662, 'The regeneration of society is the regeneration of society by individual education.', 5879, 0), (486663, 'You know, nothing is more important than education, because nowhere are our stakes higher; our future depends on the quality of education of our children today.', 12194, 0), (486664, 'When a person is humiliated, when his rights are being violated, and he does not have the proper education, naturally he gravitates toward terrorism.', 18380, 0), (486665, 'We really shouldn''t be running education like a supermarket where you 