rybody.', 13377, 0), (486813, 'If my career detour from special education to singing has done one thing, it has afforded me the opportunity to make a difference in the lives of others.', 68205, 0), (486814, 'I decided to study special education and fell in love with working with individuals with autism. That''s what I planned to do with my life.', 68205, 0), (486815, 'An inventor is simply a fellow who doesn''t take his education too seriously.', 66718, 0), (486816, 'Environmental concern is now firmly embedded in public life: in education, medicine and law; in journalism, literature and art.', 63450, 0), (486817, 'I also found that for myself, since I''ve had no religious education, it was so interesting to see the different versions of heaven and what life on earth means.', 64122, 0), (486818, 'In 1993, as House Democratic Leader, I led the fight to pass the Clinton-Gore economic plan - a plan designed to slash the deficit, invest in education, cut taxes for working families, and ask the wealthy among us to pay their fair share... Not one Republican voted for that plan. They said it was a job killer.', 69525, 0), (486819, 'Iran is not a make-believe country. It is a real country populated by some 75 million people - real people; including, I daresay, a majority who are philosophically and by education inclined toward the modern, secular world, and particularly American values.', 43433, 0), (486820, 'Responsibility educates.', 24952, 0), (486821, 'What is defeat? Nothing but education. Nothing but the first step to something better.', 24952, 0), (486822, 'Excitement in education and student productivity, the ability to get a result that you want from students, go together and cannot be separated.', 67117, 0), (486823, 'I have seen the transformative effect that education has in the lives of young women and their communities.', 68877, 0), (486824, 'Girls'' education is a human right. And along with its fundamental justice, it promises so much for the individual, for