of their ego and their manhood.', 67847, 0), (487984, '''Black Hole Sun'' was written in a car when I was driving home from the studio one night. Pretty much everything that you hear was written in my head.', 49828, 0), (487985, 'I have a Chevy Impala that I roll around in and a ''89 Jeep Wrangler, which is the first car I ever bought. It has 180,000 miles on it, and that is my daily whip. I take that everywhere. Don''t forget where you came from, that''s why I''ll never get rid of that Jeep.', 38715, 0), (487986, 'White is actually one of my favorite colors. I have a white car. I love white.', 34530, 0), (487987, 'Every system I have in my house or my car, they''re all tuned exactly the same.', 33596, 0), (487988, 'The relentless invisible storm of radio signals and electronic particles, the hustle and bustle, and the billions of petrol explosions in the engine blocks of trucks and cars seem to churn up the molecules of life and heaven so violently that the beautiful fogs are unable to hold together like they once did.', 10407, 0), (487989, 'Would this country be better off if no one drank? Yes, it would be, but we tried that; it doesn''t work. I don''t want to tell anybody that they can''t have as many drinks as they want every single night of the week as long as they don''t get behind the wheel of a car.', 68241, 0), (487990, 'If I go onstage, I want to give people everything they want and more. I''ll wash their car for them on their way out.', 60178, 0), (487991, 'Now that I have a thousand albums in my car all the time, I listen to more music. I was too lazy; I always had the same five discs in there. I''d never think to change it.', 60178, 0), (487992, 'Back when Detroit was the head of auto manufacturing, it was clear where profits were created. Right? A car was made in Detroit. There was little argument that you could make that some of the money from that should be sent overseas to Ireland.', 11321, 0), (487993, 'Even though it''s hard to learn how to back your car out the driveway at first, once it becomes a habit, you can do it almost automatically and think about something else, like the meeting that you need to go to today or what''s on the radio.', 11321, 0), (487994, 'I''m really proud of ''Cars.'' ''Cars,'' when it first came out, got probably the most mediocre reviews of a Pixar film.', 68139, 0), (487995, '''Cars'' is simply near and dear to my heart.', 68139, 0), (487996, 'I''m a car nut. My father was a parts manager at a Chevrolet dealership.', 68139, 0), (487997, 'Car love is the sound of a throaty V-8 rumbling and revving, the acceleration throwing you back in the seat - especially when you get on a beautiful, winding road and the light''s dappling through the trees.', 68139, 0), (487998, '''Cars'' is a really personal story for me because, first of all, I grew up in Los Angeles - the car crazy capital.', 68139, 0), (487999, 'Obviously, movies, you''re often on location, out in the rain or the sun, in a real place where the trees and the cars are real. But when you''re on stage, as an actor you''re imagining the environment that you''re in.', 3497, 0), (488000, 'I never listen to the radio unless I rent a car.', 115, 0);
